getImmediateHalt

public java.lang.Boolean getImmediateHalt()
The immediateHalt flag is used to indicate that no further\n rule processing should occur if a rule fails. It is an optional attribute on rule instance\n objects. In somes cases, there is no point in continuing with the application of a set \n of rules, so this flag gives the option of halting further processing.
